<h2 class="panel-title">Lecturer, Intermedia Arts</h2>
<div class="panel-meta">
  Kaywon University of Art & Design · Department of Intermedia Arts ·
  2023-Present
</div>

<div class="panel-image">
  <div class="image-slider">
    <button class="slider-btn prev" onclick="moveSlide(-1)">‹</button>
    <button class="slider-btn next" onclick="moveSlide(1)">›</button>
    <div class="slider-container">
      <img src="../images/workshop3_00.webp" alt="Kaywon Intermedia Arts" />
      <img src="../images/workshop3_01.webp" alt="Kaywon Intermedia Arts" />
      <img src="../images/workshop3_02.webp" alt="Kaywon Intermedia Arts" />
    </div>
    <div class="slider-dots">
      <span class="slider-dot active" onclick="goToSlide(0)"></span>
      <span class="slider-dot" onclick="goToSlide(1)"></span>
      <span class="slider-dot" onclick="goToSlide(2)"></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel-description">
  <p>
    Teaching courses in interactive media and electronic circuits at Kaywon
    University of Art & Design's Department of Intermedia Arts. The curriculum
    focuses on creative technology, introducing students to physical computing,
    circuit design, prototyping, and digital fabrication through hands-on
    projects.
  </p>

  <p>
    Students explore the intersection of art and technology by building
    interactive systems using Arduino, sensors, and actuators. The course
    emphasizes creative problem-solving, technical skills, and conceptual
    development, encouraging students to develop their own artistic voice
    through technology-based practice.
  </p>
</div>

